claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: A table titled 'Adults 18–49 Years of Age, Study 1' showing number of cases and rates for Flublok (N=2344) versus saline placebo (N=2304) across different case definitions (CDC-ILI with matched strains, any ILI, positive culture with any strain, subtype A, type B), with columns for Flublok vaccine efficacy (%) and 95% confidence intervals. does not support the claim because the table compares Flublok only against saline placebo and makes no mention of Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
